<P>FROM five hundred and odd thou&s;and, it has grown to &s;ix millions. It has increa&s;ed no le&s;s than twelve-fold. This is the &s;tate of the colony trade, as compared with it&s;elf at the&s;e two periods, within this century;&mdash;and this is matter for medi|tation. But this is not all. Examine my &s;econd account. See how the export trade to the colonies alone in 1772 &s;tood in the other point of view, that is, as compared to the whole trade of England in 1704. <TABLE>
